<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9281> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9281" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/8> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No. 13, pp. 214-6. His long career began with a Quaestorship, and included terms as XVir Stlitibus Iudicandis, IIIIvir Capitalis, Tribunus Plebis, Aedilis Curulis, Iudex Quaestionis, Praetor Aerarii, Proconsul of Cyprus, Curator Viarum, Proconsul of Cyprus again, and Fetialis (CIL 9.2845 = ILS 915). If Paquius' Quattuorvirate is to be dated to 44/34 B. C., and his Praetorship to 23 B. C. (as Cascione estimates), it is possible that tenure as Plebeian Tribune and Curule Aedile fell prior to 30. LM." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7503> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7503" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His quaestorship, held before being Xvir stlit. Iudic. Ex S. C., and Ivvir cap. Ex S. C., and the tr. Pl., aed. cur., all held before 23, suggest that at least he was quaestor before 31 (CIL 9.2845-ILS 915; Wiseman, NM 249, no. 308). See De Laet, 69, no. 279.\n" .
